Map generation is packaged as a loadable shared object, adv_map_gen/map_gen.so, built from the full P1 pipeline (steps 1–42) plus res_dist and whiteboard support. Run ./map_gen_lib_comp from adv_map_gen; it sources p1_build_map_gen_lib_objs.sh, compiles all pipeline objects with -fPIC, and links map_gen.so against ../data_io/runtime_static_loader_lib.so with -Wl,-rpath,'$ORIGIN/../data_io'. The host tester is built separately via ./map_gen_tester_comp, which links only map_gen_loader.cpp and does not embed the pipeline. Rebuild runtime_static_loader_lib.so in data_io if static-data definitions change before testing resource placement.

The public C API lives in map_gen_api.h; host-side dlopen wiring is in map_gen_loader.h / map_gen_loader.cpp. Shared type headers the caller may include are map_config.h (tunables, formerly P1_MapConfig), p1_map_size.h (P1_RunPrm helpers), and a forward-declared RuntimeStatics from data_io. Input is MapGenReq: seed, MapGenType (MAP_CONTINENTAL = 1 for P1), width, height, MapConfig, and an optional RuntimeStatics pointer (null means the SO self-loads statics). Output is MakeMapRslt returned by value: m_ok plus heap pointers to canonical overlays only—terrain, climate, rivers, overlay, resources—allocated inside the SO.

Typical flow: MapGenLoader::load("./map_gen.so"), fill a MapGenReq, call generate(req), copy the overlay arrays into game-owned storage, call free_rslt on the SO result, then unload() to reclaim generator memory. The loader dlopens with RTLD_GLOBAL so runtime_static_loader_lib.so symbols resolve correctly when step 42 reads static data. map_gen_generate runs the pipeline through step 42, tears down whiteboard state, and resets the res_dist statics session before returning. Do not use MakeMapRslt pointers after unload; the game keeps its copies. See map_gen_tester.cpp for a minimal end-to-end example (load, generate seed 101, copy, free, unload).
